BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:20260709-TheDeclarationisreadtoWashingtonstroops2@nyc-calendar
DTSTAMP:20260720T221926Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260709
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260710
SUMMARY:The Declaration is read to Washington's troops — 250th anniversar
 y
DESCRIPTION:The Declaration of Independence was read aloud to Continental
  Army troops assembled on the Common on July 9\, 1776\, greeted by three
  cheers.\n\nhttps://founders.archives.gov/documents/Washington/03-05-02-
 0176
URL:https://founders.archives.gov/documents/Washington/03-05-02-0176
CATEGORIES:anniversary
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:20260709-ThestatueofKingGeorgeIIIistoppled250than@nyc-calendar
DTSTAMP:20260720T221926Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260709
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260710
SUMMARY:The statue of King George III is toppled — 250th anniversary
DESCRIPTION:After the Declaration was read\, a crowd rushed to Bowling Gr
 een and pulled down the gilded lead equestrian statue of King George III
 .\n\nhttps://www.gilderlehrman.org/history-resources/essays/proclamation
 -reading-and-immediate-reception-declaration-independence
URL:https://www.gilderlehrman.org/history-resources/essays/proclamation-r
 eading-and-immediate-reception-declaration-independence
CATEGORIES:anniversary
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:20260717-TWAFlight800explodesaftertakeofffromJFK3@nyc-calendar
DTSTAMP:20260720T221926Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260717
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260718
SUMMARY:TWA Flight 800 explodes after takeoff from JFK — 30th anniversary
DESCRIPTION:TWA Flight 800 exploded off Long Island shortly after leaving
  John F. Kennedy International Airport\, killing all 230 people aboard. 
 The investigation traced the cause to a center fuel-tank explosion and d
 rove lasting changes to aviation fuel-tank safety rules.\n\nhttps://www.
 ntsb.gov/investigations/AccidentReports/Reports/AAR0003.pdf
URL:https://www.ntsb.gov/investigations/AccidentReports/Reports/AAR0003.p
 df
CATEGORIES:anniversary
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:20260719-WorldCupfinalatMetLifeStadium@nyc-calendar
DTSTAMP:20260720T221926Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260719
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260720
SUMMARY:World Cup final at MetLife Stadium
DESCRIPTION:3 p.m. ET. The largest single sporting event ever hosted in t
 he New York region. Weeks of security\, transit and crowd planning conve
 rge on this day.\n\nhttps://nynjfwc26.com/schedule/
URL:https://nynjfwc26.com/schedule/
CATEGORIES:city-life
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:20260725-NewYorkadoptsfirstUSzoningresolution110t@nyc-calendar
DTSTAMP:20260720T221926Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260725
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260726
SUMMARY:New York adopts first US zoning resolution — 110th anniversary
DESCRIPTION:New York enacted the nation's first comprehensive citywide zo
 ning law\, regulating building height\, bulk and use.\n\nhttps://www.nyc
 .gov/assets/planning/download/pdf/about/city-planning-history/zr1916.pdf
URL:https://www.nyc.gov/assets/planning/download/pdf/about/city-planning-
 history/zr1916.pdf
CATEGORIES:anniversary
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:20260827-TheBattleofLongIsland250thanniversary@nyc-calendar
DTSTAMP:20260720T221926Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260827
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260828
SUMMARY:The Battle of Long Island — 250th anniversary
DESCRIPTION:The Battle of Long Island on August 27\, 1776\, was the large
 st battle of the Revolution and a British victory that gave them New Yor
 k for the rest of the war.\n\nhttps://www.battlefields.org/learn/revolut
 ionary-war/battles/brooklyn
URL:https://www.battlefields.org/learn/revolutionary-war/battles/brooklyn
CATEGORIES:anniversary
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:20260831-OneyearuntilRikersmustclose@nyc-calendar
DTSTAMP:20260720T221926Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260831
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260901
SUMMARY:One year until Rikers must close
DESCRIPTION:Administrative Code section 4-215\, from Local Law 16 of 2021
 \, requires that by Aug. 31\, 2027 all of Rikers Island be transferred o
 ut of the Correction Department's control and no longer used to house pe
 ople. This marks exactly one year out.
CATEGORIES:justice
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:20260904-DeadlineforcharterproposalstoreachtheNov@nyc-calendar
DTSTAMP:20260720T221926Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260904
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260905
SUMMARY:Deadline for charter proposals to reach the November ballot
DESCRIPTION:Mamdani's Commission on Government Efficiency finished its 10
  public hearings and published a preliminary staff report on July 2. To 
 put charter amendments before voters on Nov. 3\, it must file them with 
 the city clerk at least 60 days beforehand. No filing date has been anno
 unced\; this is the outer bound the law implies\, not a scheduled event.
  The preliminary report points at outdoor dining\, permitting\, procurem
 ent\, bus and street infrastructure and a rainy day fund.\n\nhttps://www
 .nyc.gov/site/charter/reports/coge-reports.page
URL:https://www.nyc.gov/site/charter/reports/coge-reports.page
CATEGORIES:cityhall
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:20260908-LuigiMangionesstatemurdertrialbegins@nyc-calendar
DTSTAMP:20260720T221926Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260908
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260909
SUMMARY:Luigi Mangione's state murder trial begins
DESCRIPTION:The state trial for the killing of UnitedHealthcare chief exe
 cutive Brian Thompson in Midtown. Originally set for June 8 and moved to
  September by Judge Gregory Carro. The separate federal case\, which car
 ries the death penalty\, follows in January.
CATEGORIES:city-life
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:20260908-Free2Klaunches2000seats@nyc-calendar
DTSTAMP:20260720T221926Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260908
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260909
SUMMARY:Free 2-K launches: 2\,000 seats
DESCRIPTION:The first free 2-K seats open in four communities\, announced
  with Gov. Kathy Hochul in March\, expanding to universality within four
  years. Reporting puts services beginning in September\; no exact launch
  date has been announced\, so this is pegged to the start of the school 
 year.\n\nhttps://www.nyc.gov/mayors-office/news/2026/03/mayor-mamdani-an
 d-governor-hochul-announce-first-four-communitie
URL:https://www.nyc.gov/mayors-office/news/2026/03/mayor-mamdani-and-gove
 rnor-hochul-announce-first-four-communitie
CATEGORIES:cityhall
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:20260908-Firstdayofschool@nyc-calendar
DTSTAMP:20260720T221926Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260908
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260909
SUMMARY:First day of school
DESCRIPTION:The 2026-27 school year begins the day after Labor Day. Some 
 800\,000 children return to K-12 public school classrooms\, a number tha
 t has fallen roughly 10% since 2020.\n\nhttps://www.schools.nyc.gov/abou
 t-us/reports/nycps-data-at-a-glance
URL:https://www.schools.nyc.gov/about-us/reports/nycps-data-at-a-glance
CATEGORIES:city-life
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:20260909-FDNYceremonyforthe25thanniversaryof911@nyc-calendar
DTSTAMP:20260720T221926Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260909
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260910
SUMMARY:FDNY ceremony for the 25th anniversary of 9/11
DESCRIPTION:The official Fire Department ceremony honoring the 343 member
 s killed on Sept. 11\, 2001 and the more than 400 who have since died of
  World Trade Center-related illness. Held at the Staten Island FerryHawk
 s' stadium as part of a year-long commemoration.
CATEGORIES:city-life
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:20260911-911attacksdestroytheWorldTradeCenter25th@nyc-calendar
DTSTAMP:20260720T221926Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260911
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260912
SUMMARY:9/11 attacks destroy the World Trade Center — 25th anniversary
DESCRIPTION:Al-Qaeda hijackers crashed two jetliners into the twin towers
  of the World Trade Center\, collapsing both and killing 2\,753 people i
 n New York City. It was the deadliest terrorist attack in U.S. history.\
 n\nhttps://www.911memorial.org/911-faqs
URL:https://www.911memorial.org/911-faqs
CATEGORIES:anniversary
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:20260915-TheBritishlandatKipsBay250thanniversary@nyc-calendar
DTSTAMP:20260720T221926Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260915
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260916
SUMMARY:The British land at Kip's Bay — 250th anniversary
DESCRIPTION:British warships and troops landed at Kip's Bay on Manhattan'
 s East River shore on September 15\, 1776\, scattering American militia.
 \n\nhttps://www.mountvernon.org/library/digitalhistory/digital-encyclope
 dia/article/battle-of-kip-s-bay
URL:https://www.mountvernon.org/library/digitalhistory/digital-encycloped
 ia/article/battle-of-kip-s-bay
CATEGORIES:anniversary
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:20260916-TheBattleofHarlemHeights250thanniversary@nyc-calendar
DTSTAMP:20260720T221926Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260916
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260917
SUMMARY:The Battle of Harlem Heights — 250th anniversary
DESCRIPTION:On September 16\, 1776\, Washington won his first battlefield
  victory of the war at Harlem Heights in upper Manhattan.\n\nhttps://www
 .mountvernon.org/library/digitalhistory/digital-encyclopedia/article/bat
 tle-of-harlem-heights
URL:https://www.mountvernon.org/library/digitalhistory/digital-encycloped
 ia/article/battle-of-harlem-heights
CATEGORIES:anniversary
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:20260916-TheMetmovestoLincolnCenter60thanniversar@nyc-calendar
DTSTAMP:20260720T221926Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260916
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260917
SUMMARY:The Met moves to Lincoln Center — 60th anniversary
DESCRIPTION:The Metropolitan Opera opened its new house at Lincoln Center
 \, leaving the 1883 building on 39th Street for Wallace Harrison's grand
  modern hall.\n\nhttps://www.metopera.org/user-information/nightly-met-o
 pera-streams/articles/the-new-met/
URL:https://www.metopera.org/user-information/nightly-met-opera-streams/a
 rticles/the-new-met/
CATEGORIES:anniversary
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:20260917-Chelseabombinginjures3110thanniversary@nyc-calendar
DTSTAMP:20260720T221926Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260917
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260918
SUMMARY:Chelsea bombing injures 31 — 10th anniversary
DESCRIPTION:A pressure-cooker bomb exploded on West 23rd Street in Chelse
 a\, injuring 31 people. Ahmad Khan Rahimi was arrested days later and se
 ntenced to life in prison.\n\nhttps://www.justice.gov/archives/opa/pr/ch
 elsea-bomber-ahmad-khan-rahimi-convicted-executing-september-2016-bombin
 g-new-york-city
URL:https://www.justice.gov/archives/opa/pr/chelsea-bomber-ahmad-khan-rah
 imi-convicted-executing-september-2016-bombing-new-york-city
CATEGORIES:anniversary
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:20260918-TheNewYorkDailyTimesdebuts175thanniversa@nyc-calendar
DTSTAMP:20260720T221926Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260918
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260919
SUMMARY:The New-York Daily Times debuts — 175th anniversary
DESCRIPTION:Henry Raymond and George Jones published the first issue of t
 he New-York Daily Times\, later The New York Times.\n\nhttps://en.wikipe
 dia.org/wiki/History_of_The_New_York_Times_(1851%E2%80%931896)
URL:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/History_of_The_New_York_Times_(1851%E2%
 80%931896)
CATEGORIES:anniversary
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:20260921-TheGreatFireof1776250thanniversary@nyc-calendar
DTSTAMP:20260720T221926Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260921
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260922
SUMMARY:The Great Fire of 1776 — 250th anniversary
DESCRIPTION:A fire burned through the night into September 21\, 1776\, de
 stroying a large swath of British-occupied New York including Trinity Ch
 urch.\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Great_Fire_of_New_York_(1776)
URL:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Great_Fire_of_New_York_(1776)
CATEGORIES:anniversary
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:20260922-NathanHaleishangedasaspy250thanniversary@nyc-calendar
DTSTAMP:20260720T221926Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260922
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260923
SUMMARY:Nathan Hale is hanged as a spy — 250th anniversary
DESCRIPTION:The British hanged 21-year-old Continental officer Nathan Hal
 e as a spy in occupied New York on September 22\, 1776.\n\nhttps://conne
 cticuthistory.org/nathan-hale-hanged-in-new-york-today-in-history/
URL:https://connecticuthistory.org/nathan-hale-hanged-in-new-york-today-i
 n-history/
CATEGORIES:anniversary
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:20260922-UnitedNationsGeneralAssemblyleadersweek@nyc-calendar
DTSTAMP:20260720T221926Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260922
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260923
SUMMARY:United Nations General Assembly: leaders' week
DESCRIPTION:World leaders descend on the city for the high-level debate. 
 Major security\, traffic and diplomatic consequences for Midtown.
CATEGORIES:city-life
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:20260928-TheWhitneysBreuerbuildingopensonMadisonA@nyc-calendar
DTSTAMP:20260720T221926Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260928
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260929
SUMMARY:The Whitney's Breuer building opens on Madison Avenue — 60th anni
 versary
DESCRIPTION:Marcel Breuer's granite-clad Whitney Museum opened at 945 Mad
 ison Avenue. Its inverted-ziggurat form and cantilevered upper floors ma
 de it a landmark of Brutalist architecture.\n\nhttps://whitney.org/about
 /breuer-building
URL:https://whitney.org/about/breuer-building
CATEGORIES:anniversary
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:20260930-Federalfiscalyearendsshutdownrisk@nyc-calendar
DTSTAMP:20260720T221926Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260930
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261001
SUMMARY:Federal fiscal year ends\; shutdown risk
DESCRIPTION:Federal appropriations expire at midnight. New York City is h
 eavily exposed to disruptions in housing vouchers\, Medicaid\, transit a
 nd disaster aid.
CATEGORIES:budget
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:20261001-Newrentguidelinestakeeffect@nyc-calendar
DTSTAMP:20260720T221926Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261001
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261002
SUMMARY:New rent guidelines take effect
DESCRIPTION:Order 58 takes effect for leases beginning Oct. 1\, 2026 thro
 ugh Sept. 30\, 2027. The board adopted a rent freeze — 0% on both one- a
 nd two-year leases — delivering the central promise of Mamdani's campaig
 n.\n\nhttps://rentguidelinesboard.cityofnewyork.us/adopted-summary-of-gu
 idelines-2026-27/
URL:https://rentguidelinesboard.cityofnewyork.us/adopted-summary-of-guide
 lines-2026-27/
CATEGORIES:housing
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:20261006-TheRevolutionarybyRossBarkan@nyc-calendar
DTSTAMP:20260720T221926Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261006
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261007
SUMMARY:The Revolutionary\, by Ross Barkan
DESCRIPTION:A behind-the-scenes account of Mamdani's campaign and first m
 onths in office\, and what his win did to the city's power establishment
 . (Random House)\n\nhttps://www.penguinrandomhouse.com/books/826679/the-
 revolutionary-by-ross-barkan/
URL:https://www.penguinrandomhouse.com/books/826679/the-revolutionary-by-
 ross-barkan/
CATEGORIES:books
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:20261016-SangeropensfirstUSbirthcontrolclinic110t@nyc-calendar
DTSTAMP:20260720T221926Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261016
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261017
SUMMARY:Sanger opens first US birth control clinic — 110th anniversary
DESCRIPTION:Margaret Sanger opened the country's first birth control clin
 ic in the Brownsville section of Brooklyn.\n\nhttps://www.loc.gov/item/t
 oday-in-history/october-16/
URL:https://www.loc.gov/item/today-in-history/october-16/
CATEGORIES:anniversary
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:20261026-TheYankeesdynastybegins30thanniversary@nyc-calendar
DTSTAMP:20260720T221926Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261026
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261027
SUMMARY:The Yankees' dynasty begins — 30th anniversary
DESCRIPTION:The New York Yankees won the World Series over the Atlanta Br
 aves\, their first title since 1978 and the start of a late-1990s dynast
 y.\n\nhttps://baseballhall.org/hall-of-famers/torre-joe
URL:https://baseballhall.org/hall-of-famers/torre-joe
CATEGORIES:anniversary
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:20261028-TheStatueofLibertyisdedicated140thannive@nyc-calendar
DTSTAMP:20260720T221926Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261028
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261029
SUMMARY:The Statue of Liberty is dedicated — 140th anniversary
DESCRIPTION:President Grover Cleveland dedicated the Statue of Liberty on
  Bedloe's Island in New York Harbor.\n\nhttps://www.nps.gov/museum/exhib
 its/statue_liberty/opening_ceremony.html
URL:https://www.nps.gov/museum/exhibits/statue_liberty/opening_ceremony.h
 tml
CATEGORIES:anniversary
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:20261101-NewYorkCityMarathon50yearsofthefiveborou@nyc-calendar
DTSTAMP:20260720T221926Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261101
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261102
SUMMARY:New York City Marathon: 50 years of the five-borough course
DESCRIPTION:The 55th running of the marathon\, and the 50th anniversary o
 f the five-borough course\, which was first run in 1976 for the bicenten
 nial. It is not the 50th five-borough running — that count is 49\, becau
 se the race was cancelled in 2012 for Hurricane Sandy and in 2020 for CO
 VID-19.\n\nhttps://www.nyrr.org/media-center/press-release/2026_0203_50a
 nniversary5boromarathon
URL:https://www.nyrr.org/media-center/press-release/2026_0203_50anniversa
 ry5boromarathon
CATEGORIES:city-life
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:20261103-Generalelection@nyc-calendar
DTSTAMP:20260720T221926Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261103
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261104
SUMMARY:General election
DESCRIPTION:Governor: Hochul vs. likely Blakeman\, Congress and state leg
 islative races. No mayoral race this year. Hochul-Mamdani coordination i
 s critical for Democratic turnout.\n\nhttps://www.elections.ny.gov/
URL:https://www.elections.ny.gov/
CATEGORIES:democracy
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:20261105-TheSchaghenletterrecordsthepurchaseofMan@nyc-calendar
DTSTAMP:20260720T221926Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261105
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261106
SUMMARY:The Schaghen letter records the 'purchase' of Manhattan — 400th a
 nniversary
DESCRIPTION:A letter by Dutch official Pieter Schaghen\, dated Nov. 5\, 1
 626\, reported that colonists had 'purchased' the island of Manhattan fr
 om its Native inhabitants for goods worth 60 guilders. It is the only co
 ntemporary document of the transaction.\n\nhttps://newnetherlandinstitut
 e.org/content/peter-schagen-letter/
URL:https://newnetherlandinstitute.org/content/peter-schagen-letter/
CATEGORIES:anniversary
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:20261106-DistrictCouncil37scontractexpires@nyc-calendar
DTSTAMP:20260720T221926Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261106
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261107
SUMMARY:District Council 37's contract expires
DESCRIPTION:The 2021-2026 agreement for District Council 37\, known as DC
  37\, covers nearly 90\,000 city employees\, about a quarter of the muni
 cipal workforce. DC 37 is the city's largest union\, counting some 150\,
 000 members across sectors. The deal that replaces this one sets the pat
 tern for the teachers and everyone else\, and is the first major labor t
 est of this administration.\n\nhttps://www.nyc.gov/assets/olr/downloads/
 pdf/collectivebargaining/2021-2026/dc-37-2021-2026-moa.pdf
URL:https://www.nyc.gov/assets/olr/downloads/pdf/collectivebargaining/202
 1-2026/dc-37-2021-2026-moa.pdf
CATEGORIES:power
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:20261116-ThefallofFortWashington250thanniversary@nyc-calendar
DTSTAMP:20260720T221926Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261116
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261117
SUMMARY:The fall of Fort Washington — 250th anniversary
DESCRIPTION:British and Hessian forces captured Fort Washington\, the las
 t American stronghold on Manhattan\, on November 16\, 1776.\n\nhttps://w
 ww.battlefields.org/learn/revolutionary-war/battles/fort-washington
URL:https://www.battlefields.org/learn/revolutionary-war/battles/fort-was
 hington
CATEGORIES:anniversary
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:20261126-The100thMacysThanksgivingDayParade@nyc-calendar
DTSTAMP:20260720T221926Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261126
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261127
SUMMARY:The 100th Macy's Thanksgiving Day Parade
DESCRIPTION:A milestone parade\; the count reaches 100 in 2026 because th
 e parade was suspended during World War II. A year-long celebration camp
 aign surrounds it.
CATEGORIES:city-life
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:20261214-UNchoosesNewYorkCityforitsheadquarters80@nyc-calendar
DTSTAMP:20260720T221926Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261214
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261215
SUMMARY:UN chooses New York City for its headquarters — 80th anniversary
DESCRIPTION:The United Nations General Assembly voted to site its permane
 nt headquarters in Manhattan after John D. Rockefeller Jr. donated $8.5 
 million to buy the East River tract.\n\nhttps://www.un.org/en/about-us/h
 istory-of-the-un
URL:https://www.un.org/en/about-us/history-of-the-un
CATEGORIES:anniversary
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:20270101-Mamdanisfirstyearinoffice@nyc-calendar
DTSTAMP:20260720T221926Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20270101
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20270102
SUMMARY:Mamdani's first year in office
DESCRIPTION:One year since the inaugural address of Jan. 1\, 2026. A cust
 omary peg for retrospectives rather than a scheduled event.
CATEGORIES:cityhall
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:20270105-JuryselectioninMangionesfederaltrial@nyc-calendar
DTSTAMP:20260720T221926Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20270105
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20270106
SUMMARY:Jury selection in Mangione's federal trial
DESCRIPTION:Jury selection begins in the federal capital case before Judg
 e Margaret Garnett. Opening statements are set for Jan. 25.
CATEGORIES:city-life
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:20270116-Preliminarybudgetforfiscal2028@nyc-calendar
DTSTAMP:20260720T221926Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20270116
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20270117
SUMMARY:Preliminary budget for fiscal 2028
DESCRIPTION:Mamdani's second budget\, due under Charter section 236. Note
  the February deadline does not apply: the extension exists only in the 
 year following a mayoral election\, which was 2026.\n\nhttps://codelibra
 ry.amlegal.com/codes/newyorkcity/latest/NYCcharter/0-0-0-1
URL:https://codelibrary.amlegal.com/codes/newyorkcity/latest/NYCcharter/0
 -0-0-1
CATEGORIES:budget
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:20270201-Stateexecutivebudgetdue@nyc-calendar
DTSTAMP:20260720T221926Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20270201
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20270202
SUMMARY:State executive budget due
DESCRIPTION:In the year following a gubernatorial election\, the state co
 nstitution requires the governor's budget by Feb. 1. It determines city 
 tax authority\, transit funding and Medicaid cost-sharing — the single m
 ost consequential document of the Albany year.\n\nhttps://www.budget.ny.
 gov/
URL:https://www.budget.ny.gov/
CATEGORIES:budget
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:20270401-Statebudgetdue@nyc-calendar
DTSTAMP:20260720T221926Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20270401
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20270402
SUMMARY:State budget due
DESCRIPTION:The state constitution requires a budget by April 1. It gates
  the money for child care and for fare-free buses\, and it is the realis
 tic vehicle for any millionaire or corporate tax increase\, all of which
  require Albany.\n\nhttps://www.nysenate.gov/new-york-state-budget
